  },
  {
    id: "legal-insurance",
    title: "Legal Insurance",
    icon: `<svg class="h-8 w-8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 6l3 1m0 0l-3 9a5.002 5.002 0 006.001 0M6 7l3 9M6 7l6-2m6 2l3-1m-3 1l-3 9a5.002 5.002 0 006.001 0M18 7l3 9m-3-9l-6-2m0-2v2m0 16V5m0 16H9m3 0h3"></path></svg>`
  },
  {
    id: "3rd-pillar",
    title: "3rd Pillar",
    icon: `<svg class="h-8 w-8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 9V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2m2 4h10a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H9a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm7-5a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"></path></svg>`
  }
];

const healthFAQs = [
  {
    question: "How much does health insurance cost in Basel?",
    answer: "Health insurance premiums in Basel typically range from CHF 275-450 per month for adults, depending on the model and deductible chosen. Basel generally has slightly lower premiums than Zurich but higher than many other Swiss cantons."
  },
  {
    question: "Are there special considerations for cross-border workers in Basel?",
    answer: "Yes, cross-border workers (Grenzgänger) often have a choice (droit d'option) to be insured in Switzerland or their country of residence (France or Germany). This decision should be made carefully, considering factors like family situation and healthcare access preferences."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I easily find English-speaking doctors in Basel?",
    answer: "Yes, Basel has many English-speaking doctors and specialists. The city's international character, particularly due to the pharmaceutical industry, means that English is widely spoken in healthcare settings."
  },
  {
    question: "What are the best health insurance options for families in Basel?",
    answer: "For families in Basel, insurers like Concordia, Helsana, and Swica offer competitive family packages. Consider factors like pediatric coverage, maternity benefits, and family discounts when choosing."
  }
];

const pillarFAQs = [
  {
    question: "How much can I save on taxes with Pillar 3a in Basel?",
    answer: "The amount saved depends on your income, marginal tax rate in Basel-Stadt or Basel-Landschaft, and the amount contributed. For example, with a CHF 7,056 annual contribution, tax savings could be around CHF 1,700-2,000 depending on your income bracket."
  },
  {
    question: "What are the best 3a account options in Basel?",
    answer: "Bank 3a accounts with investment funds (e.g., VIAC, Finpension) are popular for their flexibility and potential returns. Insurance 3a products combine saving with risk coverage. The best option depends on your individual risk profile and needs."
  },
  {
    question: "Are there specific 3rd pillar considerations for cross-border workers in Basel?",
    answer: "Yes, the tax treatment of 3rd pillar contributions and benefits for Grenzgänger can be complex and depends on bilateral tax agreements. Professional advice is highly recommended for cross-border workers."
  }
];
---

<Layout
  title="Basel Insurance Guide 2025 | Health, Liability & 3rd Pillar in English"
  description="Your essential Basel insurance guide in English. Discover health (KVG), liability, household, legal, and 3rd pillar (3a/3b) options in Basel. Get local tips & advice from Expat Savvy."
>
  <!-- Schema.org markup -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" slot="head">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Article",
      "headline": "Navigating Insurance in Basel: Your Complete English Guide",
